Naphol Buranasophon
Naphol Buranasophon
HR Manager at Esthetics International Group

Responsible for the entire inventory planning, ordering, receiving, tracking and sales order processing of all brands that are marketed and distributed in EIG Thailand. Supports the Senior Management in developing an effective inventory forecasting and holding following the approved SOP in order to sustain the Company’s expansion plan as well as to achieving optimal stocks holdings.




Responsibilities

Prepares monthly inventory planning data for stock planning and replenishment;
Process inventory orders with principals on a timely basis, including issuance of purchase orders;
Creates item master in relevant system operated by the Company;
Arranges all logistics for imported stocks to ensure timely deliveries under reasonable terms;
Handles receiving process in system to ensure proper tracking of Company’s inventory;
Liaises with Warehouse department on delivery discrepancies for imported stocks and supports on inventory matters relating to Jetplus;
Submits, monitor and tracks claims with relevant principals;
Conducts review on inventory ageing and highlight items required attention to the relevant business units, and of inventory holdings to achieve optimal stock level;
Performs regular stock reconciliation between Company’s system and external data to ensure data accuracy;
Supervises the sales admin team to ensure timely and accurate order processing;
Manages the entire process of any returns from customers and consignment counters; 







Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in Supply Chain Management, Business Administration or any related field;
Preferably with 3 – 5 years’ experience in demand planning and inventory control. 
Candidates that come from the beauty or retail industries will be an added advantage;
Proficiency in MS Office especially Excel Advance is a must;
Conversant in English and able to write reasonably well is a must;
Experience with SAP B1 will be a plus;
